## 5. AUDIT CHECKLIST

### Goal vs. Delivered
- Does the delivered solution satisfy ALL requirements?
- Are there partial implementations or missing features?

### Test Results
- Are there failed tests? Why?
- Is test coverage adequate?

### Code Review Issues
- Are all code review findings addressed?
- Are there un-resolved P0/P1 items?

### Edge Cases & Robustness
- Are edge cases handled?
- Is error handling adequate?

---

## 6. ISSUE CLASSIFICATION

For each gap found, classify by severity:

| Severity | Definition | Routing Target |
|----------|-----------|---------------|
| **P0** | Directional/architectural error -- wrong foundation | Part 1.1 restart |
| **P1** | Core defect -- functionality broken or missing | Part 1.3 or 2.2 repair |
| **P2** | Quality/polish -- minor bug, style, edge case | Part 2.2 repair |

---

## 7. OUTPUT FORMAT

Write your entire output to: **`artifacts/09-issue-list.json`**

```json
{
  "audit_version": 1,
  "generated_phase": "{{ phase }}",
  "cycle": {{ cycle }},
  "overall_assessment": "PASS|NEEDS_FIXES|BLOCKED",
  "summary": "One paragraph summary of audit findings",
  "issues": [
    {
      "id": "{{ phase }}-001",
      "severity": "P0|P1|P2",
      "title": "Short title",
      "description": "Detailed description",
      "source": "requirements_gap|test_failure|code_review|edge_case",
      "affected_files": ["src/file.py"],
      "fix_strategy": "How to fix",
      "is_design_level": true|false
    }
  ]
}
```

